text:
The capacity of biogas plants in Ukraine amounted to 70 MW

04 Nov 2019, 19:53

At the end of Q3 2019, 70 MW of biogas plants were installed in Ukraine. This was reported in the State Agency for Energy Efficiency and Energy Saving.
The department notes that 47 MW - work on agricultural waste, and 23 MW - in landfills.
As the experience of the leading countries of the world (Germany, Denmark and others) shows, biogas production is an extremely profitable business, which allows:

dispose of waste in agricultural enterprises;
reduce landfill volumes;
generate energy for own needs of enterprises;
replace gas consumption;
receive organic fertilizers for agriculture;
reduce harmful emissions.

“In order to stimulate the development of this sphere in Ukraine, in 2015 a“ green ”tariff for electricity from biogas at the level of 12.39 eurocents / kWh was introduced,” the State Agency said.

